:"Tante scuse","vote_average":6.8,"vote_count":2},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/dWLOqsdYwaYtzaIsakkkqlTk97x.jpg","genre_ids":[35,18],"id":1370,"origin_country":["GB"],"original_language":"en","original_name":"Scully","overview":"Scully was a British television drama with some comedy elements set in the city of Liverpool, England, that originated from a BBC Play For Today episode \"Scully''s New Years Eve\". Originally broadcast on Channel Four in 1984, the single series was spread over six half-hour episodes plus a one-hour final episode. It was written by playwright Alan Bleasdale. The drama is notable for featuring many of the Liverpool football club first-team squad of that era.\n\nFrancis Scully is a teenage boy who has his heart set on gaining a trial match for Liverpool to hopefully fulfil his ambition of playing for the club. Francis, in everyday situations during his waking hours, occasionally \"sees\" famous Liverpool players such as Kenny Dalglish when they are not really there. These dream-like sequences recur throughout the episodes.\n\nThe main plotline is the efforts of Scully''s school teachers to persuade Scully to appear in the school pantomime which they attempt by promising him a trial with his beloved Liverpool if he will cooperate. When Scully and his friends are not in school making trouble for the teachers and the school caretaker, they are seen roaming the local streets upsetting the neighbours and getting into trouble with the police. Scully sometimes has visions of the school caretaker appearing as a vampire due to the caretaker''s nickname being Dracula. These frequent waking dream sequences give the show a somewhat surreal atmosphere.","popularity":2.244,"poster_path":"/fAp2XA1G6LkW5Rj0mNapVLcCf6o.jpg","first_air_date":"1984-05-14","name":"Scully","vote_average":5.3,"vote_count":3},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/mhAAKXSYnQe7Hj6lMJeJsTNMUQj.jpg","genre_ids":[18],"id":230248,"origin_country":["IE"],"original_language":"ga","original_name":"Scúp","overview":"Set in a struggling Irish language newspaper in Belfast, the series is built around the character of Rob Cullan. a journalist who has left a high flying job in an English newspaper under a cloud. He is persuaded to return to the community he grew up in by the wily newspaper proprietor Diarmuid Black to help rescue his ailing publication.","popularity":2.4796,"poster_path":"/6oTUaNLqXHajuev0hn7wfuczKMB.jpg","first_air_date":"2013-02-27","name":"Scúp","vote_average":0,"vote_count":0},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"genre_ids":[35],"id":112923,"origin_country":["US"],"original_language":"en","original_name":"SCUM","overview":"Tim and Eric present a grotesquely surreal anthology of discarded sketches, found footage, musical numbers, and 3D animation.","popularity":0.794,"poster_path":"/u2f7k2XFaaXCFVg2OrI1LQLzHpd.jpg","first_air_date":"2019-07-16","name":"SCUM","vote_average":0,"vote_count":0},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/a2Pm6x7jpJkfLzdMSQqG3XcfM0A.jpg","genre_ids":[80,18],"id":75697,"origin_country":["GB"],"original_language":"en","original_name":"The Sculptress","overview":"When author Rosalind Leigh is assigned to write a book about the life of Olive Martin, a woman sentenced to life in prison for killing her mother and sister, she develops a relationship with Olive and is soon convinced of her innocence. With the help of restaurant owner and former policeman Hal Hawksley, she sets out to prove it and undo what she sees as a miscarriage of justice.","popularity":1.4131,"poster_path":"/pyICjSheNnu4p2HvXPiDHr2sqZz.jpg","first_air_date":"1996-02-24","name":"The Sculptress","vote_average":6,"vote_count":1},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"genre_ids":[35],"id":4959,"origin_country":["GB"],"original_language":"en","original_name":"Attention Scum","overview":"Attention Scum! was a 2001 television comedy series created by Simon Munnery and Stewart Lee. It starred Munnery as his \"The League Against Tedium\" character and contained acerbic stand-up routines atop a transit van and sketches including mainstays such as \"24 Hour News\", operatic intermissions by Kombat Opera, and two characters engaged in a duel over their hats.","popularity":0.6766,"poster_path":"/ox7nNYqYz5fbigrz1jTJB5AECvl.jpg","first_air_date":"2001-02-25","name":"Attention Scum","vote_average":5.5,"vote_count":2},{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/qAE5q6pchO2Y3HhP4fHUlyiIYzr.jpg","genre_ids":[],"id":220903,"origin_country":["US"],"original_language":"en","original_name":"Scuba Jake","overview":"Take a dive with treasure hunter and scuba fanatic Jake Koehler! From uncovering murder weapons to returning lost technology and sunken engagement rings, there is never a dull moment in Scuba Jake''s aquatic adventures.","popularity":0.0193,"poster_path":"/gJM9GyX4EaDW9VbErzntwtYa8HJ.jpg","first_air_date":"2022-01-01","name":"Scuba Jake","vote_average":0,"vote_count":0}],"total_pages":5,"total_results":85}','2026-04-07 04:17:32');
